==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seismal
<hw>Seis"mal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>seismo`s</grk> an earthquake, from
<grk>sei`ein</grk> to shake.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to an
earthquake; caused by an earthquake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Seismic vertical</b></col>, <cd>the point upon the
earth's surface vertically over the center of effort or focal point
whence the earthquake's impulse proceeds, or the vertical line
connecting these two points.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seismogram</ent>⟦br⟧
